<subSubSection id="C34065587A27FFB7FF1E022E35D5B134" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BE536D37A27FFB7FF1E022E35BCB294" blockId="9.[151,760,774,2045]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FF1E022E35B4B414" bold="true" box="[151,389,774,797]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">
Redescription. 
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FEC5022E35B4B414" bold="true" box="[332,389,774,797]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">Body</emphasis>
</emphasis>
length 
<quantity id="4CA29B367A27FFB7FE56022E3608B414" box="[479,569,774,797]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
, maximum body width 1.0 mm. Head and labrum black, pronotum and elytra uniformly yellowish; legs reddish to yellowish. 
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FF1E024E34E3B474" bold="true" box="[151,210,870,893]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">Head</emphasis>
with weak microsculpture on interstices; punctation sparse, each puncture bearing pointed seta. Eyes separated by 3.1× the width of one eye in dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FD0E028E36C9B4B4" bold="true" box="[647,760,934,957]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">Pronotum</emphasis>
with sparse setiferous punctation similar to that on head; interstices with weak microsculpture. 
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FDC702CE36A4B4F4" bold="true" box="[590,661,998,1021]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">Elytra</emphasis>
with 10 striae sharply impressed except anteromedially (near scutellar shield) where neither striae nor serial punctures are visible; interval punctation sparse, setiferous; interstices without distinct microsculpture. 
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FE73054E3656B374" bold="true" box="[506,615,1126,1149]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">Aedeagus</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13612A567A27FFB7FDFC054E3688B374" box="[629,697,1126,1149]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[151,182,1941,1960]" captionTargetBox="[165,1398,197,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-13@8.[157,1431,189,1911]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Male genitalia of Thysanarthria species. A–E – T. atriceps (Régimbart, 1903) from Zambia: 20 km W of Gwanda, coll. NMPC (A–C – whole aedeagus in dorsal, lateral and ventral view; D–E – detail of median lobe and parameres in dorsal and ventral view); F–J – T. atriceps from Republic of South Africa: 8 km NEE of Stanford, coll. NMPC (F–H – whole aedeagus in dorsal, lateral and ventral view; I–J – detail of median lobe and parameres in dorsal and ventral view); K–O – T. brittoni Balfour-Browne, 1951, holotype (K–M – whole aedeagus in dorsal, lateral and ventral view; N–O – detail of median lobe and parameres in dorsal and ventral view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4488930" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4488930/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">Figs 4</figureCitation>
K–O) c. 
<quantity id="4CA29B367A27FFB7FF3B05AE3534B394" box="[178,261,1158,1181]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
long. Phallobase strongly widened at base of parameres, c. as wide as bases of parameres combined, strongly constricted at c. midlength, slightly bent in lateral view. Paremere widely rounded basally, slightly narrowing in apical third, apex rounded, apices divergent from each other. Median lobe narrow, membranous apically, without subapical projections; apex reaching c. level of apex of parameres; gonopore transversely oval, situated in distal third.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE536D37A27FFB7FF1E048E35D5B134" blockId="9.[151,760,774,2045]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FF1E048E352BB2B4" bold="true" box="[151,282,1446,1469]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">Variability.</emphasis>
BALFOUR- BROWNE (1951) mentions that the dorsal microsculpture of the head and pronotum, which is very weakly developed in the 
<typeStatus id="54E188717A27FFB7FE7204CE366CB2F4" box="[507,605,1510,1533]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">holotype</typeStatus>
, is stronger in some of the 
<typeStatus id="54E188717A27FFB7FE96072E35B6B114" box="[287,391,1542,1565]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">paratypes</typeStatus>
which are hence externally undistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D507A27FFB7FEE3070E35ECB134" baseAuthorityName="Regimbart" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[362,477,1574,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Thysanarthria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atriceps">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FEE3070E35ECB134" box="[362,477,1574,1597]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">T. atriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34065587A27FFB7FF1E076E3649B074" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE536D37A27FFB7FF1E076E3649B074" blockId="9.[151,760,774,2045]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FF1E076E3660B154" bold="true" box="[151,593,1606,1629]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">Differential diagnosis and discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D507A27FFB7FDD5076E34D8B174" authorityName=": HEBAUER" authorityYear="1997" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Thysanarthria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brittoni">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FDD5076E34D8B174" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">Thysanarthria brittoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D507A27FFB7FE4B074E3609B174" baseAuthorityName="Regimbart" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[450,568,1638,1661]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Thysanarthria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atriceps">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FE4B074E3609B174" box="[450,568,1638,1661]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">T. atriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in all characters including male genitalia, which only differ in the proportions of the parameres including their slightly diverging apices, and by the more strongly constricted phallobase (see under 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D507A27FFB7FE9907CE35B5B1F4" baseAuthorityName="Regimbart" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[272,388,1766,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Thysanarthria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atriceps">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FE9907CE35B5B1F4" box="[272,388,1766,1789]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">T. atriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for details). The difference of the genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D507A27FFB7FE92062E35B8B014" authorityName=": HEBAUER" authorityYear="1997" box="[283,393,1798,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Thysanarthria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brittoni">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FE92062E35B8B014" box="[283,393,1798,1821]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">T. brittoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the examined specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D507A27FFB7FF1E060E3536B034" baseAuthorityName="Regimbart" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[151,263,1830,1853]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Thysanarthria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atriceps">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FF1E060E3536B034" box="[151,263,1830,1853]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">T. atriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is bigger than the observed intraspecific variability of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D507A27FFB7FF7B066E3555B054" baseAuthorityName="Regimbart" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[242,356,1862,1885]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Thysanarthria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atriceps">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FF7B066E3555B054" box="[242,356,1862,1885]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">T. atriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is the reason why we consider 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A4D507A27FFB7FF1E064E3535B074" authorityName=": HEBAUER" authorityYear="1997" box="[151,260,1894,1917]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Thysanarthria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brittoni">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FF1E064E3535B074" box="[151,260,1894,1917]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">T. brittoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a separate species at the moment.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34065587A27FFB7FF1E06AE355FB094" box="[151,366,1926,1949]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BE536D37A27FFB7FF1E06AE355FB094" blockId="9.[151,760,774,2045]" box="[151,366,1926,1949]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FF1E06AE34C5B094" bold="true" box="[151,244,1926,1949]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">Biology.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C34065587A27FFB7FF1E068E34EFB0F4" pageId="9" pageNumber="238" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE536D37A27FFB7FF1E068E34EFB0F4" blockId="9.[151,760,774,2045]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">
<emphasis id="B92EEAC17A27FFB7FF1E068E3503B0B4" bold="true" box="[151,306,1958,1981]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only known from the 
<typeStatus id="54E188717A27FFB7FDCF068E3647B0B4" box="[582,630,1958,1981]" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">type</typeStatus>
locality in western 
<collectingCountry id="F34D76437A27FFB7FF7E06EE3577B0D4" box="[247,326,1990,2013]" name="Yemen" pageId="9" pageNumber="238">Yemen</collectingCountry>
, Arabian Peninsula (BALFOUR- BROWNE 1951).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
